[[File:Saesee_and_Clones_Attack.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Clone marines accompany [[Saesee Tiin/Legends|Saesee Tiin]] on a mission to board ''[[Prosperous/Legends|Prosperous]]'' during the [[Battle of Coruscant/Legends|Battle of Coruscant]].]]
'''Clone marines''' were elite [[Clone trooper/Legends|clone troopers]] of the [[Republic Navy/Legends|Republic Navy]] tasked with warding off [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Separatist]] boarding parties on [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Republic]] [[Capital ship/Legends|capital ships]], as well as conducting boarding action against Separatist [[Starship/Legends|vessels]].

The clone marine's weapons consisted of a [[DC-15A blaster rifle/Legends|DC-15A blaster rifle]], a [[PLX-1/Legends|PLX-1]] [[Missile launcher/Legends|rocket launcher]], a [[commando pistol]] based on the design of a [[DC-15S/Legends|DC-15S]], and [[V-1 thermal detonator|V-1]] [[Thermal detonator/Legends|thermal detonators]]. This infantry [[unit]] would enter an enemy ship and would either capture or critically damage essential systems on that ship. On boarding parties, they would be more reliable, due to their quick sharpshooting and automatic DC-15A [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]] [[Blaster rifle/Legends|rifles]], than a [[Clone trooper pilot/Legends|clone pilot]] armed with a [[Blaster pistol/Legends|blaster pistol]]. On some occasions, the marines would land a [[Realspace/Legends|space]] [[Transport/Legends|transport]] in an enemy hangar and deploy from there or use [[Jetpack/Legends|jetpacks]] to fly through space and land on the ship itself.

